                <div class="text-input-row label-left">
                  <span class="text-input-label">Filter</span>
                  <div style="flex: 1;">
                    <div class="text-input-field">
                      <input type="text" value="Some entered text" />
                      <span class="text-input-clear"><svg width="14" height="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg></span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Helper Row -->
          <div class="demo-container" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
            <div class="demo-toolbar">
              <div class="demo-toolbar-left"><div class="demo-theme-pill">Helper Row</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="demo-canvas" style="gap: 24px; align-items: flex-start;">
              <!-- Helper + Counter -->
              <div class="text-input-demo">
                <div class="text-input-row label-left">
                  <span class="text-input-label">Username <span class="required">*</span></span>
                  <div style="flex: 1;">
                    <div class="text-input-field">
                      <input type="text" placeholder="Enter username" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-input-helper">
                      <span class="text-input-helper-text">Must be 3-20 characters</span>
                      <span class="text-input-counter">0/20</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <!-- Error Helper -->
              <div class="text-input-demo">
                <div class="text-input-row label-left">
                  <span class="text-input-label">Email <span class="required">*</span></span>
                  <div style="flex: 1;">
                    <div class="text-input-field error">
                      <input type="text" value="invalid-email" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-input-helper">
                      <span class="text-input-helper-text error">
                        <svg width="12" height="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4"/><path d="M12 16h.01"/></svg>
                        Please enter a valid email address
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <!-- Success Helper -->
              <div class="text-input-demo">
                <div class="text-input-row label-left">
                  <span class="text-input-label">Domain <span class="required">*</span></span>
                  <div style="flex: 1;">
                    <div class="text-input-field success">
                      <input type="text" value="mysite.com" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-input-helper">
                      <span class="text-input-helper-text success">
                        <svg width="12" height="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                        Domain is available
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Do & Don't -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="do-dont" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul>
                <li>Always use Label Position = Left as the default layout on desktop.</li>
                <li>Switch to Label Position = Top on responsive/mobile breakpoints.</li>
                <li>Always provide a label for the input field.</li>
                <li>Use placeholder text to show example input format, not as a replacement for the label.</li>
                <li>Use helper text to provide context, formatting requirements, or constraints.</li>
                <li>Show the character counter when there is a maximum length.</li>
                <li>Use the Error state with a descriptive helper text message.</li>
                <li>Use prefix/suffix elements to clarify expected input format.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul>
                <li>Don't use Label Position = Top as the default on desktop.</li>
                <li>Don't use placeholder text as the only label.</li>
                <li>Don't show Error and Success states simultaneously.</li>
                <li>Don't use the Read Only state when the field should be Disabled.</li>
                <li>Don't add both prefix text and prefix icon simultaneously unless design calls for it.</li>
                <li>Don't use overly long helper text.</li>
                <li>Don't hide the label in forms where context is not obvious.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>


      </div> <!-- End tab-overview -->


      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <!-- TAB: STYLE                                  -->
      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-style" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">
        <h2 id="style-overview" class="doc-section-title">Style</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design tokens, variant axes, and visual specifications that define the Text Input's visual language.</p>

        <!-- Variant Axes -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="variant-axes" class="doc-section-title">Variant Axes</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Text Input component is defined by four variant axes that combine to produce the full set of design variants.</p>
          <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;">
            <div style="font-size: 15px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.7;">
              <strong>3</strong> Sizes &times; <strong>8</strong> States &times; <strong>2</strong> RTL &times; <strong>2</strong> Label Positions = <strong style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-size: 18px;">96 variants</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Sizes -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="sizes" class="doc-section-title">Sizes</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Three sizes to fit different layout contexts and information density requirements.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Size</th><th>Min Height</th><th>Padding</th><th>Font Size</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Small</strong></td><td>32px</td><td>6px 10px</td><td>13px</td><td>Compact forms, table inline editing</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Medium</strong></td><td>36px</td><td>8px 12px</td><td>14px</td><td>Default for most forms</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Large</strong></td><td>44px</td><td>10px 14px</td><td>16px</td><td>Standalone forms, registration pages</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- States -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="states" class="doc-section-title">States</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Text Input cycles through eight states, each with distinct visual treatments to communicate interactivity and validation.</p>
          <div class="state-grid">
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid #C8CDD8; border-radius:8px; background:var(--prism-surface); font-size:13px; color:#8B95A9;">Placeholder</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Default</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Border: #C8CDD8, bg: white</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid #8B95A9; border-radius:8px; background:var(--prism-surface); font-size:13px; color:#8B95A9;">Placeholder</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Hover</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Border darkens to #8B95A9</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid #2C66DD; border-radius:8px; background:#fff; box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(44,102,221,0.15); font-size:13px; color:#8B95A9;">Placeholder</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Focus</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Blue border + focus ring</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid #C8CDD8; border-radius:8px; background:var(--prism-surface); font-size:13px; color:#1A1A2E;">Entered text</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Filled</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Text color: #1A1A2E</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid #C1181B; border-radius:8px; background:var(--prism-surface); font-size:13px; color:#1A1A2E;">Invalid</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Error</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Border: #C1181B, red helper</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid #0C8844; border-radius:8px; background:var(--prism-surface); font-size:13px; color:#1A1A2E;">Valid</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Success</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Border: #0C8844, green helper</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid #E3E7ED; border-radius:8px; background:#F5F6F8; font-size:13px; color:#8B95A9; opacity:0.6;">Disabled</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Disabled</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Bg: #F5F6F8, 60% opacity</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border:1px solid transparent; border-radius:8px; background:#F5F6F8; font-size:13px; color:#1A1A2E;">Read only</div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Read Only</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Bg: #F5F6F8, no border</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Label Position -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="label-position" class="doc-section-title">Label Position</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Two label positioning options for different layout scenarios.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Position</th><th>Layout</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Left</strong></td><td>Label inline with the input, horizontally aligned</td><td>Default for standard desktop forms</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Top</strong></td><td>Label stacked above the input field</td><td>Responsive/mobile layouts, narrow side panels</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Design Tokens -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="design-tokens" class="doc-section-title">Design Tokens</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Tokens used for text input styling across states and themes.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Property</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>border-default</code></td><td>Border color</td><td>#C8CDD8</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>border-hover</code></td><td>Border hover</td><td>#8B95A9</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>border-focus</code></td><td>Border focus</td><td>#2C66DD</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>border-error</code></td><td>Border error</td><td>#C1181B</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>border-success</code></td><td>Border success</td><td>#0C8844</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>bg-disabled</code></td><td>Disabled background</td><td>#F5F6F8</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-input</code></td><td>Input text color</td><td>#1A1A2E</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-placeholder</code></td><td>Placeholder color</td><td>#8B95A9</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-helper</code></td><td>Helper text color</td><td>#5F6C89</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-label</code></td><td>Label text color</td><td>var(--prism-text)</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>focus-ring</code></td><td>Focus ring shadow</td><td>0 0 0 3px rgba(44, 102, 221, 0.15)</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>radius/radius-s</code></td><td>Border radius</td><td>8px</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <!-- TAB: USAGE                                  -->
      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <!-- When to Use -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When to Use</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Use the Text Input component in the following scenarios.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Single-line text entry:</strong> For collecting short free-text input such as names, emails, URLs, or descriptions.</li>
            <li><strong>Form fields:</strong> As the primary building block for data collection forms across the application.</li>
            <li><strong>Search:</strong> Combined with a prefix search icon for search bars and filter inputs.</li>
            <li><strong>Filters:</strong> In data table toolbars and dashboards for filtering content inline.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Label Position Guidelines -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="label-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Label Position Guidelines</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Best practices for choosing the right label position across breakpoints and layouts.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Desktop default:</strong> Always use Label Position = Left. This is the standard layout for desktop forms with sufficient horizontal space.</li>
            <li><strong>Responsive breakpoints:</strong> Auto-switch to Label Position = Top when the viewport width drops below the mobile breakpoint or when the form is inside a narrow container.</li>
            <li><strong>Narrow side panels:</strong> Use Label Position = Top when the text input appears inside drawers, side panels, or modal forms with limited width.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Prefix & Suffix Elements -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="prefix-suffix" class="doc-section-title">Prefix &amp; Suffix Elements</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for using prefix and suffix elements to enhance input context.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Element</th><th>Position</th><th>Example</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Prefix Icon</strong></td><td>Leading</td><td>Search icon, mail icon</td><td>Provide visual context for the input purpose</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Prefix Text</strong></td><td>Leading</td><td>$, https://</td><td>Show fixed format prefix values</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Suffix Text</strong></td><td>Trailing</td><td>kg, .com, %</td><td>Show units or domain suffixes</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Suffix Icon</strong></td><td>Trailing</td><td>Calendar icon, dropdown arrow</td><td>Indicate secondary action or picker</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Clear Button</strong></td><td>Trailing (rightmost)</td><td>X icon</td><td>Allow quick clearing of entered content</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- RTL Support -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="rtl-support" class="doc-section-title">RTL Support</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Text Input component fully supports right-to-left (RTL) layouts for Arabic, Hebrew, and other RTL languages.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Layout mirrored:</strong> The entire input layout mirrors horizontally. Label moves to the right, input field aligns accordingly.</li>
            <li><strong>Prefix/suffix swap:</strong> Prefix elements appear on the right side and suffix elements on the left side in RTL mode.</li>
            <li><strong>Text alignment:</strong> Input text and placeholder text automatically right-align in RTL mode.</li>
            <li><strong>Helper row:</strong> Helper text starts from the right, counter moves to the left.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Related Components -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="related-components" class="doc-section-title">Related Components</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used alongside the Text Input.</p>
          <div class="related-grid">
            <a href="Text-area.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18"/><path d="M9 21V9"/></svg> Text area</a>
            <a href="Select.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"/><polyline points="8 10 12 14 16 10"/></svg> Select</a>
            <a href="Search.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><path d="M21 21l-4.35-4.35"/></svg> Search</a>
            <a href="Date-picker.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M16 2v4M8 2v4M3 10h18"/></svg> Date picker</a>
            <a href="Form.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg> Form</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Figma Reference -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="figma-reference" class="doc-section-title">Figma Reference</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The source-of-truth design file for the Text Input component.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Figma Node:</strong> <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">16042:44400</code> — Component Set: Text Input</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Feedback -->
        <div id="feedback-usage" class="feedback-banner" style="display: none;">
          <div><div class="fb-text">Was this page helpful?</div><div class="fb-sub">Help us improve by sharing your feedback on this component's documentation.</div></div>
          <div style="display: flex; gap: 10px;"><button class="feedback-btn">Not helpful</button><button class="feedback-btn primary">Yes, helpful</button></div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <!-- TAB: CODE                                   -->
      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-code" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <style>
          .code-playground { border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; background: var(--prism-surface); margin-bottom: 40px; }
          [data-theme="light"] .code-playground { background: #fff; border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.1); box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(37,99,235,0.08); }
          .cp-toolbar { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; padding: 16px 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); background: var(--prism-surface-hover); }
          [data-theme="light"] .cp-toolbar { background: rgba(248,250,255,0.6); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.1); }
          .cp-control-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; flex: 1; min-width: 120px; }
          .cp-label { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text-muted); }
          .cp-select { background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text); padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 8px; outline: none; font-family: inherit; font-size: 14px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; }
          [data-theme="light"] .cp-select { background: #fff; border-color: rgba(37,99,235,0.15); color: #1e293b; }
          .cp-select:focus { border-color: var(--prism-violet); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(37,99,235,0.15); }
          .cp-preview { padding: 60px; min-height: 200px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: #0a0a0c; background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255,255,255,0.1) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 20px 20px; transition: background 0.3s ease; }
          [data-theme="light"] .cp-preview { background: #fff; background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(37,99,235,0.08) 1px, transparent 1px); }
          .cp-code-header { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 12px 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border-top: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); }
          [data-theme="light"] .cp-code-header { background: rgba(248,250,255,0.8); border-color: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); }
          .cp-action-btn { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; background: transparent; border: none; font-family: inherit; font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--prism-text-muted); cursor: pointer; padding: 6px 12px; border-radius: 6px; transition: all 0.2s; }
          .cp-action-btn:hover { background: var(--prism-surface-hover); color: var(--prism-text); }
          .cp-code-area { background: #0a0a0c; padding: 24px; overflow-x: auto; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #e2e8f0; }
        
  /* ══ Mobile responsive (added globally) ══ */
  .nav-hamburger { display: none; background: transparent; border: none; color: var(--prism-text); padding: 8px; margin-right: 8px; cursor: pointer; border-radius: 8px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; }
  .nav-hamburger:hover { background: var(--prism-surface-hover); }
  .sidebar-backdrop { display: none; position: fixed; inset: 0; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5); z-index: 95; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.25s ease; }
  .sidebar-backdrop.open { display: block; opacity: 1; }
  .sidebar-mobile-nav { display: none; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .nav { padding: 0 16px; height: 64px; justify-content: flex-start; gap: 4px; }
    .nav-links { margin-left: auto; }
    .nav-hamburger { display: inline-flex; order: -1; margin-right: 4px; }
    .nav-logo-mark { font-size: 22px; }
    .nav-logo-sub { font-size: 9px; }
    .nav-links > a,
    .nav-links > .nav-dropdown,
    .nav-links > div[style] { display: none !important; }
    .nav-links { gap: 0; }

    .components-layout { display: block; padding-top: 64px; grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .sidebar { position: fixed; top: 64px; left: 0; width: 300px; max-width: 86vw; height: calc(100vh - 64px); max-height: none; padding: 20px 18px 32px; border-right: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-bottom: none; overflow-y: auto; transform: translateX(-100%); transition: transform 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1); z-index: 96; background: var(--prism-black); }
    [data-theme="light"] .sidebar { background: #ffffff; }
    .sidebar.open { transform: translateX(0); box-shadow: 12px 0 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.25); }
    body.sidebar-locked { overflow: hidden; }

    .sidebar-mobile-nav { display: block; margin: 0 -18px 16px; padding: 0 18px 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); }
    .sidebar-mobile-nav h4 { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: 12px; padding-left: 4px; }
    .sidebar-mobile-nav ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
    .sidebar-mobile-nav a { display: block; padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 8px; transition: all 0.2s ease; }
    .sidebar-mobile-nav a:hover { background: var(--prism-surface-hover); color: var(--prism-violet); }
    .sidebar-mobile-nav a.active { color: var(--prism-violet); background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); }

    .main-panel { padding: 24px 20px 48px; grid-column: auto; grid-row: auto; }
    /* mobile-width-safety v4 — collapse any inline grid on narrow viewports */
    .main-panel, .main-content-inner, .main-content-area { max-width: 100%; width: 100%; box-sizing: border-box; min-width: 0; }
    .main-content-inner > *, .doc-section, .doc-section > * { max-width: 100%; box-sizing: border-box; min-width: 0; }
    .main-content-inner img, .main-content-inner svg:not(.inline-svg) { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
    .main-content-inner pre, .main-content-inner code { white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word; }
    .main-content-inner pre { overflow-x: auto; }
    .anatomy-diagram { overflow: visible !important; padding: 48px 40px !important; zoom: 0.82; }
    .anatomy-diagram > * { max-width: 100%; }
    .demo-container { overflow: hidden; }
    .demo-canvas { padding: 32px 20px !important; overflow-x: auto; }
    .code-playground, .cp-code-area { overflow-x: auto; }
    /* Foundation inner-page grids: collapse every multi-column inline grid */
    [style*="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr)"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr)"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr)"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns: 320px 1fr"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr"] { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
    /* Flex rows with heavy fixed widths should wrap */
    [style*="display: flex"][style*="gap"] { flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .main-content-area { display: flex; flex-direction: column; grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .main-content-inner { padding-bottom: 32px; }
    .toc-sidebar { display: none; }

    .page-header-area .page-title,
    .page-title { font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.15; }
    .page-desc { font-size: 16px; }
    .doc-section h2, .doc-section-title { font-size: 22px; }

    .do-dont-grid,
    .illus-type-grid,
    .comp-grid,
    .density-grid,
    .illus-showcase-grid,
    .pattern-category-grid,
    .tone-grid,
    .voice-traits,
    .principles-grid,
    .theme-grid,
    .message-grid,
    .weight-grid,
    .pattern-grid,
    .collection-grid,
    .anti-pattern-list,
    .dodont-grid,
    .icon-metaphor-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }

    table { display: block; overflow-x: auto; }
    .size-table, .token-table, .anatomy-table, .doc-table, .tone-table { display: block; overflow-x: auto; white-space: nowrap; min-width: 0; }

    .feedback-banner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 16px; padding: 24px; }
    .illus-type-card { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
    .illus-type-preview { min-height: 180px; padding: 24px 16px; }

    /* Component detail page grids */
    .state-grid,
    .anatomy-grid,
    .usecase-grid,
    .anat-legend,
    /* Zia Experience hub grids */
    .zia-prompt-grid,
    /* Resource hub grids */
    .lib-grid,
    .lib-grid-logo,
    .lib-grid-illust { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; gap: 12px !important; }

    /* Inline-styled 2- or 3-column grids */
    [style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr)"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr)"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr)"],
    [style*="grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)"] { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }

    /* Resource hub outer padding */
    .page-content { padding: 88px 16px 48px !important; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .nav { padding: 0 12px; height: 60px; }
    .components-layout { padding-top: 60px; }
    .sidebar { top: 60px; height: calc(100vh - 60px); }
    .nav-logo-mark { font-size: 20px; }
    .main-panel { padding: 18px 14px 36px; }
    /* mobile-width-safety v3 */
    .main-panel { padding: 16px 10px 24px !important; }
    .anatomy-diagram { padding: 40px 28px !important; overflow: visible !important; zoom: 0.66; }
    .demo-canvas { padding: 24px 12px !important; }
    .page-header-area .page-title,
    .page-title { font-size: 26px; }
    .page-desc { font-size: 15px; }
    .sidebar-heading { font-size: 10px; }
    .search-shortcut { display: none; }
    .page-content { padding: 72px 12px 32px !important; }
  }
</style>

        <h2 id="live-demo-code" class="doc-section-title">Live demo (Code)</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Configure the Text Input component and view generated HTML.</p>
        <div class="code-playground">
          <div class="cp-toolbar">
            <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Size</label><select class="cp-select" id="tf-pg-size"><option value="sm">Small</option><option value="md" selected>Medium</option><option value="lg">Large</option></select></div>
            <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">State</label><select class="cp-select" id="tf-pg-state"><option value="default" selected>Default</option><option value="hover">Hover</option><option value="focus">Focus</option><option value="filled">Filled</option><option value="error">Error</option><option value="success">Success</option><option value="disabled">Disabled</option><option value="readonly">Read Only</option></select></div>
            <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Label Position</label><select class="cp-select" id="tf-pg-label"><option value="top" selected>Top</option><option value="left">Left</option></select></div>
            <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Show Helper</label><select class="cp-select" id="tf-pg-helper"><option value="true" selected>Yes</option><option value="false">No</option></select></div>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-preview" id="tf-pg-preview"></div>
          <div class="cp-code-header">
            <div style="font-size:13.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);">HTML</div>
            <button class="cp-action-btn" id="tf-pg-copy"><svg width="15" height="15" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8 7v8a2 2 0 002 2h6M8 7V5a2 2 0 012-2h4.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l4.414 4.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V15a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2M8 7H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h8a2 2 0 002-2v-2"/></svg> Copy code</button>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-code-area" id="tf-pg-code"></div>
        </div>
        <script>
        (function(){
          var els={size:document.getElementById('tf-pg-size'),state:document.getElementById('tf-pg-state'),label:document.getElementById('tf-pg-label'),helper:document.getElementById('tf-pg-helper')};
          var previewArea=document.getElementById('tf-pg-preview');
          var codeOut=document.getElementById('tf-pg-code');
          var copyBtn=document.getElementById('tf-pg-copy');
          function esc(s){return s.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;').replace(/"/g,'&quot;');}
          function update(){
            var sz=els.size.value,st=els.state.value,lp=els.label.value,showHelper=els.helper.value==='true';
            var sizeClass='text-input-'+sz;
            var isDisabled=st==='disabled';
            var isReadonly=st==='readonly';
            var stateClass=st==='default'?'':' '+st;
            var fieldClass='text-input-field'+(st==='focus'?' focus':'')+(st==='error'?' error':'')+(st==='success'?' success':'')+(isDisabled?' disabled':'')+(isReadonly?' readonly':'');
            var val=st==='filled'||st==='error'||st==='success'?'Entered value':'';
            var placeholder=val?'':'Placeholder';
            var helperText=st==='error'?'This field is required':st==='success'?'Looks good!':'Helper text';
            var helperClass='text-input-helper-text'+(st==='error'?' error':'')+(st==='success'?' success':'');

            // Preview
            var h='<div class="text-input-demo '+sizeClass+'" style="width:100%;max-width:360px;">';
            h+='<div class="text-input-row label-'+lp+'">';
            h+='<span class="text-input-label">Label <span class="required">*</span></span>';
            h+='<div style="flex:1;"><div class="'+fieldClass+'">';
            h+='<input type="text" '+(val?'value="'+val+'"':'placeholder="'+placeholder+'"')+(isDisabled?' disabled':'')+(isReadonly?' readonly':'')+'>';
            h+='</div>';
            if(showHelper){
              h+='<div class="text-input-helper"><span class="'+helperClass+'">'+helperText+'</span><span class="text-input-counter" style="font-size:12px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);">0/100</span></div>';
            }
            h+='</div></div></div>';
            previewArea.innerHTML=h;

            // Code
            var code='<div class="text-input" data-size="'+sz+'">\n';
            code+='  <label class="text-input-label">Label <span class="required">*</span></label>\n';
            code+='  <div class="text-input-field">\n';
            code+='    <input\n      type="text"\n';
            if(val) code+='      value="'+val+'"\n';
            else code+='      placeholder="Placeholder"\n';
            if(isDisabled) code+='      disabled\n';
            if(isReadonly) code+='      readonly\n';
            if(st==='error') code+='      aria-invalid="true"\n      aria-describedby="helper-1"\n';
            code+='    />\n  </div>\n';
            if(showHelper){
              code+='  <div class="text-input-helper"'+(st==='error'?' id="helper-1" role="alert"':'')+'>\n';
              code+='    <span class="text-input-helper-text'+(st==='error'?' error':'')+'">'+helperText+'</span>\n';
              code+='    <span class="text-input-counter">0/100</span>\n';
              code+='  </div>\n';
            }
            code+='</div>';
            codeOut.innerHTML=esc(code)
              .replace(/class=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">class</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/type=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">type</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/value=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">value</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/placeholder=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">placeholder</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/data-size=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">data-size</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/aria-invalid=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">aria-invalid</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/aria-describedby=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">aria-describedby</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/id=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">id</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/role=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">role</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>')
              .replace(/ disabled/g,' <span style="color:#f97316;">disabled</span>')
              .replace(/ readonly/g,' <span style="color:#f97316;">readonly</span>')
              .replace(/&lt;(\/?)(div|label|input|span)(.*?)&gt;/g,'&lt;$1<span style="color:#a78bfa;">$2</span>$3&gt;');
          }
          Object.values(els).forEach(function(e){e.addEventListener('change',update);});
          copyBtn.addEventListener('click',function(){
            var r=document.createElement('div');r.innerHTML=codeOut.innerHTML;
            navigator.clipboard.writeText(r.innerText).then(function(){
              var o=copyBtn.innerHTML;copyBtn.innerHTML='<svg width="15" height="15" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg> Copied!';setTimeout(function(){copyBtn.innerHTML=o;},2000);
            });
          });
          update();
        })();
        </script>

        <hr class="doc-divider"/>

        <h2 id="component-properties" class="doc-section-title">Component Properties</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">All configurable properties exposed on the Text Input Figma component, grouped by function.</p>

        <!-- Label & Required -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="label-required" class="doc-h3">Label &amp; Required<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">3 props</span></h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>Label Text</code></td><td>String</td><td>"Label"</td><td>The visible label for the input field.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Show Label</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>true</td><td>Controls whether the label is visible.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Required</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Shows the asterisk (*) indicator next to the label.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Prefix Elements -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="prefix-elements" class="doc-h3">Prefix Elements<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">4 props</span></h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>Prefix Icon</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show a leading icon in the input field.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Prefix Icon Instance</code></td><td>Instance Swap</td><td>Search</td><td>The icon component used for the prefix.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Prefix Text</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show static prefix text (e.g., "$").</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Prefix Text Value</code></td><td>String</td><td>"$"</td><td>The prefix text string displayed.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Input Content -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="input-content" class="doc-h3">Input Content<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">2 props</span></h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>Input Text</code></td><td>String</td><td>""</td><td>The editable text content of the input.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Placeholder</code></td><td>String</td><td>"Placeholder"</td><td>Hint text shown when the input is empty.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Suffix Elements -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="suffix-elements" class="doc-h3">Suffix Elements<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">7 props</span></h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>Suffix Text</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show static suffix text (e.g., "kg").</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Suffix Text Value</code></td><td>String</td><td>"kg"</td><td>The suffix text string displayed.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Suffix Icon</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show a trailing icon in the input field.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Suffix Icon Instance</code></td><td>Instance Swap</td><td>Chevron</td><td>The icon component used for the suffix.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Suffix Icon Right</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show an additional rightmost trailing icon.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Suffix Icon Right Instance</code></td><td>Instance Swap</td><td>Info</td><td>The icon component used for the right suffix.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Clear Button</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show the clear (X) button to reset input content.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Helper Row -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="helper-row" class="doc-h3">Helper Row<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">6 props</span></h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>Show Helper</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>true</td><td>Controls visibility of the helper row.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Helper Icon</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show an icon alongside the helper text.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Helper Icon Instance</code></td><td>Instance Swap</td><td>Info</td><td>The icon component used for helper.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Helper Text</code></td><td>String</td><td>"Supporting text"</td><td>Guidance or validation message below the input.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Show Counter</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Show character count on the right of the helper row.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Counter Text</code></td><td>String</td><td>"0/100"</td><td>The character count display string.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Variant Axis Reference -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="variant-axis-reference" class="doc-section-title">Variant Axis Reference</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">All four variant axes that define the component set in Figma.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Axis</th><th>Values</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Size</strong></td><td>Small, Medium, Large</td><td>Medium</td><td>Controls the overall dimensions and font size of the input.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>State</strong></td><td>Default, Hover, Focus, Filled, Error, Success, Disabled, Read Only</td><td>Default</td><td>Controls the visual and interaction state of the component.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>RTL</strong></td><td>false, true</td><td>false</td><td>Mirrors the layout for right-to-left languages.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Label Position</strong></td><td>Left, Top</td><td>Left</td><td>Controls whether the label is inline or stacked above.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Instance Overrides -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="instance-overrides" class="doc-section-title">Instance Overrides</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Step-by-step guide for overriding the Text Input instance in Figma.</p>
          <ol class="numbered-list">
            <li>Drag the Text Input component from the Assets panel onto your canvas.</li>
            <li>Select the instance and open the Properties panel on the right sidebar.</li>
            <li>Choose the desired <strong>Size</strong> (Small, Medium, or Large) from the variant axis dropdown.</li>
            <li>Set the <strong>State</strong> axis to match the interaction context (Default, Hover, Focus, Filled, Error, Success, Disabled, or Read Only).</li>
            <li>Toggle <strong>RTL</strong> to true if the form is rendered in a right-to-left language.</li>
            <li>Set <strong>Label Position</strong> to Left (desktop) or Top (responsive/mobile).</li>
            <li>Override the <strong>Label Text</strong>, <strong>Placeholder</strong>, and <strong>Helper Text</strong> string properties to match the field's purpose.</li>
            <li>Enable or disable <strong>Prefix Icon</strong>, <strong>Prefix Text</strong>, <strong>Suffix Text</strong>, <strong>Suffix Icon</strong>, <strong>Clear Button</strong>, and <strong>Counter</strong> as needed.</li>
            <li>Swap icon instances (Prefix Icon Instance, Suffix Icon Instance) to the appropriate icons from the icon library.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <!-- TAB: ACCESSIBILITY                          -->
      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-accessibility" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">
        <h2 id="accessibility-overview" class="doc-section-title">Accessibility</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for ensuring all text input interactions are accessible across assistive technologies and input modalities.</p>

        <!-- Color Contrast -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="color-contrast" class="doc-h3">Color Contrast<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(34,197,94,0.15); color: #16a34a;">WCAG AA</span></h3>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>Input text (#1A1A2E) on white background maintains a contrast ratio of <strong>15.1:1</strong>, exceeding WCAG AAA requirements.</li>
            <li>Placeholder text (#8B95A9) on white background maintains a minimum contrast ratio of <strong>3.5:1</strong> for non-text UI elements.</li>
            <li>Error state border (#C1181B) meets the <strong>3:1</strong> minimum for UI component contrast against white.</li>
            <li>Helper text (#5F6C89) on white background maintains at least <strong>4.6:1</strong> contrast ratio for small text.</li>
            <li>Label text uses the page's primary text color to ensure maximum readability.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Keyboard Navigation -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="keyboard-navigation" class="doc-h3">Keyboard Navigation</h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Key</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>Tab</code></td><td>Move focus to the text input (or to the next focusable element).</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Shift + Tab</code></td><td>Move focus to the previous focusable element.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Escape</code></td><td>Clear the input field (when clear button is enabled) or blur the field.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Enter</code></td><td>Submit the form (when the input is inside a form element).</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Arrow keys</td><td>Move the text cursor within the input content.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Screen Reader -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="screen-reader" class="doc-h3">Screen Reader</h3>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>Always associate the <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;label&gt;</code> element with the input using the <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">for</code> attribute matching the input's <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">id</code>.</li>
            <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-describedby</code> to link helper text and error messages to the input so screen readers announce them.</li>
            <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-required="true"</code> on required fields to communicate obligation to assistive technologies.</li>
            <li>Prefix and suffix text should be included via <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label</code> or visible label context so the format is clear (e.g., "Price in dollars").</li>
            <li>The clear button should have an explicit <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label="Clear input"</code> for screen reader users.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Error Handling -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="error-handling" class="doc-h3">Error Handling</h3>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-invalid="true"</code> on the input element when the field is in the Error state.</li>
            <li>Error messages must be linked via <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-describedby</code> so the error is announced when the input receives focus.</li>
            <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-live="polite"</code> on error message containers for real-time validation so errors are announced dynamically.</li>
            <li>Do not rely solely on color (red border) to indicate errors. Always pair with a descriptive text message.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- RTL Accessibility -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="rtl-accessibility" class="doc-h3">RTL Accessibility</h3>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">dir="rtl"</code> on the container or use CSS <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">direction: rtl</code> to ensure proper layout mirroring.</li>
            <li>Ensure tab order remains logical in RTL mode (right-to-left reading order).</li>
            <li>Verify that screen readers announce label and helper text in the correct reading direction.</li>
            <li>All interactive elements (clear button, suffix icons) must remain reachable via keyboard in RTL layouts.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Disabled & Read Only -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="disabled-readonly" class="doc-h3">Disabled &amp; Read Only</h3>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Disabled:</strong> Use the native HTML <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">disabled</code> attribute. The input is removed from tab order and cannot receive focus.</li>
            <li><strong>Read Only:</strong> Use the native HTML <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">readonly</code> attribute. The input remains focusable and its value can be copied, but it cannot be edited.</li>
            <li>If a disabled field needs to explain <em>why</em> it is disabled, use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-disabled="true"</code> instead of the native <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">disabled</code> attribute so it remains focusable for tooltip access.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Label Position A11y -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="label-position-a11y" class="doc-h3">Label Position</h3>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>Regardless of visual label position (Left or Top), the <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;label&gt;</code> must always be programmatically associated with its input.</li>
            <li>When the label is visually hidden for design reasons, use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label</code> or a visually-hidden label element to maintain screen reader support.</li>
            <li>Label Position = Top may improve readability for screen magnifier users who zoom into narrow viewports.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      </div><!-- close main-content-inner -->

